<p>Welfare Comm membership is free.&nbsp;</p><p>The committee meets at 6:30pm on Fridays in the JCR lounge.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Welfare Comm works with the Welfare team (welfare officer and three assistants) to run awareness campaigns that occur throughout the year. From deciding what a campaign week should aim to achieve to helping with putting on events for students, the committee is vital in making sure campaigns occur. Upcoming campaigns can be seen&nbsp;<a href="http://community.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/welfare/information">here.</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The committee also aims to work with various members of college to help in anyway that welfare can. For example, to aid the Student Disabilities Rep and LGBT reps when they are putting on events.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Anyone is welcome to join welfare committee, welfare is important to everyone!</p><p>&nbsp;</p>